    <item>
      <title></title>
      <link>https://isekulic.github.io/home/about.html</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 20 Apr 2016 00:00:00 +0200</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://isekulic.github.io/home/about.html</guid>
      <description>Biography I am a recent graduate in Computer Science from a small town near Zagreb, Croatia. I&amp;rsquo;m currently taking a dive into the wonderful world of academia as a Research Associate (or if you like &amp;ndash; an Intern) at Heidelberg Institute for Theoretical Studies.
My research topic is a continuation of the master thesis, where I studied the language of authors affected by bipolar disorder on Reddit. We&amp;rsquo;ve provided a benchmark results for bipolar disorder prediction and analyzed significant differences in psycholinguistic and emotion-related features between the bipolar and the control group.</description>
    </item>
    
